 Bhisho - The Eastern Cape Provincial Government notes the judgement of the Grahamstown division of the High Court of South Africa on the matter brought to it by the Unemployed People's movement. "Given the nature of the matter at issue, the provincial government is studying the judgement to understand the specifics of the judgement and the order made by the High Court," said Mvusiwekhaya Sicwetsha, Spokesperson for Eastern Cape Premier, Oscar Maabuyane. "After government has completed studying this judgement, a decision on the steps to be taken by the Provincial government regarding this matter will be communicated soon." Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 